<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={5.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={8.58}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={7.90}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={5.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={8.58}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={7.90}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>35.02</li><li>79.94</li><li>62.72</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}^{{2}}={8.58}^{{2}}+{7.9}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({8.58}\right)}{\left({7.9}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{25}={73.6164}+{62.41}-{135.564}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{111.0264}=-{135.564}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.81899619367974}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={35.015565232064}={35.02}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({35.015565232064}\right)}}}}{{5.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{8.58}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.75880904327502}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left(-{0.75880904327502}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={79.944471257362}\approx{79.94}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{35.015565232064}+{79.944471257362}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={62.721964892542}\approx{62.72}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

